data.content:
noun
/ˌmɛtəˈmoɚfəsəs/ , pl -phoses /-fəˌsiːz/
a major change in the appearance or character of someone or something [count]
We have watched her metamorphosis from a shy schoolgirl into a self-confident businesswoman.
a company that has gone through a series of metamorphoses [noncount]
The government has undergone political metamorphosis since his election.
biology :a major change in the form or structure of some animals or insects that happens as the animal or insect becomes an adult [noncount]
the metamorphosis of tadpoles into frogs
The class learned about how caterpillars undergo metamorphosis to become butterflies. [count]
caterpillars undergoing metamorphoses

Danh từ
(số nhiều metamorphoses /,metə'mɔ:fəsi:z/)
sự biến hoá
(sinh vật) [sự] biến thái
